title: The Real World
author: karissa
text: as i lay in the bright green grass,  i feel like i'm in my own room.  underneath my head is a pillow made of long grass.  i look up into the sky.  it almost looks like a tv screen.  the bright,  baby-blue background,  and the white fluffy clouds.  the clouds look like characters.  a dog,  a girl,  a mom and a dad,  flowers,  and then the main character. . .          the sun.     the sun is bright,  brighter then the sky.  the sun is full of life.  i feel like i am far away in a different place.      soon it get's dark.  the sky. . .  it's not still.  the sun leaves.  the moon comes.  the moon is round,  a perfect sphere.  it glows.  there are many stars in the sky,  up,  up,  amd far away.  it feels like the stars are in a ballroom dancing,  laughing,  and. . .  soon i get a feeling inside.  now,  i am up with the stars dancing.  the moon,  now on the other side.  i can't see it.  a star flies over to me.  he then asks,  '' do you want to dance?''    i get up.  i dance.  music,  in my head,  is playing a lovely tune.  i wish this night would never end.  i dance to a couple more songs,  and then the moon comes and says ''leave!'' in a strong,  stern voice.  so,  i step down and sit up.  my dad is standing there.  he says ''let's go home. ''    we do and as i'm leaving i see a star.  it's moving slowly.  it looks like it's waving.  i'll wave back.     the next morning,  as i'm walking to the bus stop,  i looked up into the sky,  and said. . .         ''what a beautiful day it is. ''

title: How to Forgive
author: kate
text: when tears are raindrops there must be a cause.  is it hurt or pain? or is it nothing at all? is it a tremendous brawl? or a minuscule disagreement? is it about what you think it is? or is it much more? will it be blown away within wind? shall it be everlasting? you look to me for answers,  but they are all inside.  don't think with your head and be lost,  think with your soul and be free.  doesn't your heart ache to forgive and grasp forgiveness.  don't let common sense get in the way of heart and soul.  if you did you would become ignorant.  for it is not the wind that can blow away your problems,  but your own breath.

title: Life as a Rock
author: kate
text: there i sit,  solitary,  still.  waiting for days,  weeks,  even months for someone to pick me up,  feel my smoothness,  the smoothness from the millions of waves that washed upon me.  splashing and roaring,  booming and crashing.  picked up once or twice by a giggling little girl or a freckled little boy.  picked up,  then thrown back in again and again.  until someone found  me.  they didn't throw  me in like everyone else.  they wrapped me up with care and  put me in a suitcase.  not a rock anymore,  but a memory.  and now. . .  here i sit- solitary,  still.

text: the attic lays barren,  except for the red stain on the cracked window in the corner,  and the window from which the ghost looks out of.  the floorboard creak,  and so do the steps.  the light bulb glows neon blue,  though it was meant to be white.  some dust clumps are in the corner,  trying to cover the mouse and ant traps,  already full.  an old burnt down candle is in the brass holder,  the tip orange,  as if it was just used.  a deserted beehive is on the ceiling,  a few dead hornets lay around it,  determined to protect their dead queen.  the only life is the owner's daughter,  checking on the ghosts,  stuck up there for eternity.  she walks around,  seeing gun shots and knife stabs in the wall,  hoping that the spirits are good,  and don't come to hurt her.  she sees the white wisp of an apparition,  sensing its sadness,  feeling its pain.  she leaves,  full of grief,  not knowing that something,  someone,  followed her.

title: Endless Hopes and Broken Dreams
author: kristysha
text: i sit thinking, thinking about my life.  here i sit and wait in a dark,  cold room of sadness.  my world is one of broken dreams and tears of pain and sorrow.  everytime i see the sun i hope my world would change but instead it stays the same dark,  cold,  scary.  i wait for god to take me up to the heavens and bring me light and hope.  but everytime i think, i think why?  why can't i have life and joy? in my world i have nothing.   just broken dreams and darkness.  no light is shed on my pale gray face.  i cry,  just cry to see other children play and run in the sun.  the earth has come to swallow me up and kill the little spark of light; hope i have.  nobody cares about my world.  my world of broken dreams and darkness. . .

title: The Black Rose
author: kristysha
text: once,  a girl gave her very best friend a black rose.  she said it symbolized their friendship.  strong, bold, special, ever-lasting yet,  complex.  they would have small fights and big fights but they always patched-up again.  they knew everything about each other.  even their deepest,  darkest secrets.    then,  one faithful day,  that all suddenly changed.  those 2 special friends drifted aparted.  she,  who gave the black rose cried all day and night.  the rose withered and the petels blew in the wind slowly.  the leaves drooped and fell 1 by 1 off the thorny stem.  the stem broke in 2.  like the stem of the rose,  the girl broke too.  they never saw each other again. . .   (this poem is dedicated to my sister and best-friend,  felicia in singapore. she was a very special friend but now we are ''drifting apart. '' felicia,  i hope you read this poem. )

title: Fairytale To Me
author: krystal
text: the day i met you,  i knew it was all a dream.  you're eyes so blue,  was almost like a fairytale to me.  as we became closer,  they only became bluer,  as if the fairytale was only getting better.  as we became best friends forever,  there was a slight sparkle in his eyes,  almost like when cinderella met the prince.  after he chased me,  and caught me,  i held on.  and as soon as i held on.  his eyes only became sparklier and bluer as the fairytale went on.  when i had him,  i much only liked his eyes.  for his eyes were as beautiful as the stars up above.  we started losing distance,  and stopped talking for a while.  i wondered why this was so,  these things never happen in fairytales.  the day i finally saw him again,  was like when my fairytale had just began.  only,  there was something different about my fairytale,  was it me,  or was it him? his eyes weren't as blue,  or as sparkly as the stars.  they were only darker,  like only deep thoughts,  of the truth.  i finally stopped looking at his eyes,  and then i saw something,  that was a big surprise.  he was sitting in a wheelchair,  for his legs were all cut,  and his hands were all bruised.  he told me what happened,  as i started to cry.  he then started speaking low,  as if he were about to die.  and the saddest thing he said,  was goodbye.  was i not realizing what was happening in life,  was i just focusing on his wonderful,  blue eyes.  now i realize what i shouldn't of done.  why did i think that a fairytale was to come,  because fairytales end in happy endings,  unlike this one.  my fairytale was all a mistake,  to think it'd be great.  but i now see that it's all reality,  and not everything is great.  so now i just have to get over the fact,  that there are no happy endings,  and no matter how much we believe in fairytales as a kid,  we will finally grow up and see.  that in life,  all you'll realize,  is that your fairytale,  is your worst dream.

title: A Christmas to Remember
author: kyle
text: have you ever had a christmas when the â“starâ” just didnâ’t shine? or when there were no lights on that fresh christmas pine? and instead of a gift from the north pole,  all you find is a big lump of coal? your long awaited presents from uncles and aunts,  turn out to be socks and a stiff pair of pants?  well,  this year my christmas started almost like that.   when i was first woken up by my sister,  the â“bratâ”! she jumped on my bed and stepped on my head,  â“itâ’s too early to get up,  little sister!â” i said.  yet,  i walked from my room to our bright christmas tree,  and when i entered the room,  oh,  what did i see?  our christmas tree bare,  balls on the floor,  the carpet was covered in needles galore! â“we gave you one job!â” my parents said to me,  â“to make sure and water our wonderful tree! now look at whatâ’s happened! the tree is so bare.  our christmas is ruined because you didnâ’t care!â”  i looked at my family all glaring at me,  then told them,  â“christmas is not found in a tree,  or in decorations so shiny and bright,  or stockings all hung by the warm firelight.  itâ’s not the presents that we give or receive.  no,  it is none of these things,  i believe. â”                                                                                    â“christmas is family and being together,  sharing our blessings now and forever.  we have each other and a warm loving home.  there are many less fortunate,  spending christmas alone.  who cares if our tree is bare and brown? at least itâ’s still standing,  it didnâ’t fall down!â”    the silence that followed made me a little uneasy.  the sight of our tree made me feel a bit queasy.  but my family soon put all these worries to rest,  as they smiled and agreed with what i had expressed.  our christmas that year was one to remember,  but my sister will water the tree next december!

title: The Googlebogent

text: there once were two brothers,  one bob and one rob.  bob was a neat freak,  and rob was a slob.   these two brothers,  both loved to invent,  and together they made,  a googlebogent.   this googlebogent,  was for all of your needs: it could cook you a feast,  and could pick all your weeds.   they wanted it to cook,  for those who needed food,  and to teach all the children,  not to be rude.   but the king of this land,  was full of much greed,  and he wanted it,  to fix his every need.   he forced bob a rob,  to hand it right over,  and he thought he was the smartest,  in his land of tover.   yet he wasnâ’t smart,  no,  not smart at all,  for nobody was needed,  hence they emptied each hall.   now the king was alone,  with no one in sight,  and he knew what he did,  was not very bright.  finally the king,  bored out of his mind,  did something unexpected,  and extremely kind.   he gave the googlebogert,  every single part,  to the people of his kingdom,  with a very big heart.   now weâ’re ending our story,  on a bright,  happy note,  since the once-greedy king,  learned not to gloat.

text: ''is he my guy?'' i said with a sigh.  i watch him play,  in the middle of may and sometimes in fall,  playing basketball.  i say,  ''is he my guy,  anyway?''  he walks in the park,  leaning against a tree's bark,  waiting for me,  and that's what i see.  ''is he my guy or is it just another lie?'' i see him walking.  i see him talking,  but what do i say,  ''is he my guy,  anyway?''  frustrated over this,  not knowing if i'm his.  ''is he my guy?'' he said,  ''no'' with a sigh and i asked,  ''why?'' saying ''no'' was a big lie.  it was just a jest  because he was being a pest.  ''he was always my guy. ''
